{"cursor":"13713","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n{{Infobox person |name = Burnie Burns |image = Burnie Burns, 2011 Portrait.jpg\n|caption = Burnie Burns, 2011 Portrait |birthname = Michael Burns |birth_date =\n|birth_place = Rochester, New York, U.S. |nationality = American |occupation =\nActor, Writer, Film Producer, Film Director |employer = Rooster Teeth\nProductions |yearsactive = 2003âpresent |salary = |networth = |spouse = Jordan\nBurns (Divorced) |children = 2 |website = |footnotes = }} 'Michael \"Burnie\"\nBurns' (born 1973) is an American independent filmmaker living in Austin, Texas.\nHe is best known for his contributions in Machinima, a form of filmmaking that\nuses a real-time 3D engine, although he has also worked with\nanimation and live action. In April 2003, Burns, along with several\nfriends and co-workers, created the Internet machinima series [[Red vs. Blue|Red\nvs. Blue: The Blood Gulch Chronicles]]. Filmed using the video games [[Halo:\nCombat Evolved|Halo]], [[Halo 2]], [[Halo 3]], [[Halo: Reach]], and [[Halo 4]],\nRed vs. Blue was acclaimed for its humor and originality, making Burns an\nInternet celebrity. His success allowed him to\nco-found the production company Rooster Teeth Productions. After the immediate popularity of Red vs Blue, Burns\nattracted the attention of video game company Electronic Arts, who asked him to\ncreate a promotional series using their upcoming game, [[The Sims 2]]. The\nresult was [[The Strangerhood]]. Burns also premiered [[PANICS|P.A.N.I.C.S.]], a\nmini-series that utilizes the [[F.E.A.R. (computer game)|F.E.A.R.]] game engine.\nAs one of the innovators in the field of machinima, he has made guest\nappearances at the Penny Arcade Expo, San Diego Comic-Con International,\nSundance and The Sydney Film Festival. {{cite web\n|date=April 23, 2012|url=http://journalists.org/event/ona-austin-producing-great-video-for-the-\nweb/ |title=ONA Austin: Producing Great Video for the Web |work=Online News\nAssociation |accessdate=May 6, 2012}} For his work on [[Immersion\n(series)|Immersion]] (2010), a live action series that tests video game tropes\nin the real world, he has been nominated for an IAWTV award in the \"Best Hosted\nTaped Web Series\" category.\n","linknr":255,"url":"Burnie_Burns","recorded":1375058751,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Burnie_Burns&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Burnie_Burns&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.flaggedRevs.basic%7Cext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf10/extensions/FlaggedRevs/frontend/modules/img/doc-magnify.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf10/extensions/FlaggedRevs/frontend/modules/img/arrow-down.png","/wiki/Wikipedia:Pending_changes","//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Log&type=review&page=Burnie_Burns","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Michael_Burns_(disambiguation)","/wiki/Wikipedia:Protection_policy#pc1","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Padlock-silver-light.svg/20px-Padlock-silver-light.svg.png","/wiki/File:Burnie_Burns,_2011_Portrait.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Burnie_Burns%2C_2011_Portrait.jpg/220px-Burnie_Burns%2C_2011_Portrait.jpg","/wiki/Rochester,_New_York","/wiki/United_States_of_America","/w